The '''Pavilhão Welwitschia Mirabilis''' is a state-owned multisports indoor arena located in [[Moçâmedes]], [[Angola]]. The 3072-seat arena, features hardwood flooring, electronic scoreboard and a wide range of features that makes it one of the most modern of its kind in Africa.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.portalangop.co.ao/angola/pt_pt/noticias/desporto/2013/8/36/Caracteristicas-tecnicas-Pavilhao-Welwitschia-Mirabilis,c6b7f35b-4ade-4938-be63-2a83acc23dd4.html |title=Características técnicas do Pavilhão Welwitschia Mirabilis |publisher=ANGOP.com |date=2013-09-06 |accessdate=2014-04-28|language=pt}}</ref> was built to host the [[2013 FIRS Men's Roller Hockey World Cup|2013 World Roller Hockey World Championship]] alongside the [[Pavilhão Multiusos de Luanda]]. It is fit for such sports as [[Basketball]], [[Team handball|Handball]], [[Volleyball]] and [[Roller Hockey]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://desporto.sapo.pt/hoquei/mundial2013/artigo/2013/09/06/angola_inaugurado_pavilh_o_welw.html |title=Inaugurado pavilhão Welwitschia Mirabilis |date=2013-09-06 |accessdate=2014-04-19|language=pt}}</ref>

The arena was named after [[Welwitschia]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.portalangop.co.ao/angola/en_us/noticias/desporto/2013/8/36/Welwitschia-mirabilis-pavilion-unveiled,d56d5535-a318-4124-bd35-d4189122b4b3.html |title=Welwitschia mirabilis pavilion unveiled |publisher=ANGOP.com |date=2013-09-07 |accessdate=2014-04-30}}</ref> a plant [[Endemism|endemic]] to the [[Namib desert]] in [[Angola]] with such a huge life span that some believe to be as long as 2000 years.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://mundialhoqueiangola2013.com/index.php?option=com_k2&view=item&id=5:a-provincia-do-namibe-situa-se-no-litoral-sul-de-angola&lang=pt |title=PAVILHÃO WELWITSCHIA MIRABILIS |publisher=ANGOP.com |accessdate=2014-04-28|language=pt}}</ref>

